text: the new season has started and this is a very popular subreddit  so on sunday nights we often have threads popular enough to hit rall so even if you avoid rthewalkingdead until you can watch the new episode  you might see threads on your front page  we have our subreddit setting set to not show thumbnail images next to links  but your profile preferences might override our settings allowing you to see spoilery screencaps you d rather not see  to prevent this  make sure you click on the  preferences   https  wwwredditcomprefs  link to the right of the snoo on the top navigation bar  and under  media  select  do not show thumbnails next to links  then click on the  save options  button at the bottom of the preferences menu now you wo nt see any screencaps from the episode until you actually click on a link  as always  if you do see links with spoilers in the title or untagged comic spoilers in show threads  click the report button so the mods can remove them if necessary  enjoy the new season

text: was the savior s weaponry in the comics  the saviors were shown with exclusively handheld closecombat weapons for some time before they were revealed to have guns and long range weaponry this was highlighted by negan saying something along the lines of  i bet you figured we did nt have any guns wrong  rick was under the assumption that the saviors had limited battle options because of the juxtaposition of the two group s weaponry  but it turns out  the saviors were just as equipped as the alexandrians rick crafted his plan of attack under this belief until the shock came and it was revealed he was wrong  accentuating his fear of the threat at hand and forcing the reevaluation of his confrontational strategies  this ca nt happen in the show  as the saviors have already been seen with guns i get that it makes sense in the context of the events playing out on the tv adaption  but it was fun to watch the threat of the saviors unfold and become more pronounced as time went by in the comics  this particular nuance being one of the reveals to further impound that

text: absolutely  everyone who s quick to call this the best episode ever is just happy that the show decided to do some action for once all of the fan favorite episodes have been like that  just like the opener to season 5 and the end to season 2  3  and 4 there were multiple mistakes in the directing  most notably being the  day night transition  the ignoring of last seasons cliffhanger  the whole maggie situation the show is really going downhill in quality  every season has been the same thing opening episode is amazing  mid season finale is amazing then the mid season premiere is amazing and the season finale is amazing in between we have two half decent episodes and then all filler this combined with how unnatural the dialogue is now is turning off a lot of viewers  for me personally  glenn has pissed me off to no end they have great ideas but just ca nt execute well glenn s fall into the horde was shot terribly and did nt respect the continuity of the previous shot  his survival at terminus was bs  his survival in the woods in the finale last season  his survival tonight by literally the biggest stretch of the entire show so far  i love these characters and the world they re in  but the writing and directing needs to improve if they want this show to last clearly the fans will continue watching  but critically i m predicting a large decline as the seasons pass i still love the show  but mistakes and decisions like these are ruining the experience

text: meet their end in the season finale   1 daryl this is the most obvious for me  with daryl now being the one who killed negan s scouting party  the symbolism of the blood on his wings  and the promise that we ll see more of him this second half norman reedus is also getting more and more movie deals  so i m sure his time is up he s been the fan favorite for nearly 5 years  and i m sure the writers  gimple  and kirkman have been cooking this up for a while  which may be the biggest blow to the show since hershel s death   2 glenn part of me prefers him to die  as it would have the most impact storywise  and  given the context of the comics  it s possibly the single greatestmost horrifying introduction to a villain in comic book history  but i feel like they re only teasing him dying and being saved at the last minute just to trick all the comic readers into being set in their expectations i think that they think that we think it s the most obvious thing to do  and most people expect to see that on their screens  but  they do nt want to follow the comics exactly in this case  which leads into   3 morgan this is the most interesting choice for me there s some  morgan sacrifices himself in place of x   theories  which i feel would lend some great kudos to the writers  but  i do nt think would work out at all  given the villain we re expecting it would make sense for morgan to beg and plead for him to die instead  as he has no real family left  and many of the group have been having major trouble with him  even though in s6e09 he claims to finally have realized what he now needs to do in order to stay in the group   it would be the ultimate sacrifice  but i do nt think negan would have any of that shit he is nt emotional  forgiving  or really logical in most cases  so i highly doubt he d just go  oh  yeah  sorry about that  x   i ll take this guy instead bring him up   4 spencer i do nt think he ll be present when negan shows up  but i feel like it would be similar to my morgan scenario spencer has no family anymore and does nt have any significant other that we know of in alexandria the only reason why i even put him in on the list  really low  at that  is because he is nt a major character in any way  and is more likely a candidate for his comic death   5 abraham this is the one i doubt the most kirkman himself has said that he regrets killing him off so early  and that he wishes he would have been around for the allout war arc  so i feel like he wo nt be getting the arrow death nor meet lucille anytime soon i expect him to be gone by the end of the show s adaptation of the allout war arc  maybe as the season 7 finale or season 8 midseason finale  anywhere between season 7 and 9  really

text: i think the point was supposed to be that she was stuck up there with a swarm of walkers underneath her and no easy way to get down without injury or getting eaten if you are stuck somewhere for hours  are you going to choose to stay on the larger platform with railings and room to sitlay down  and a better vantage point of your surroundings  or are you going to choose to stand on a skinny metal railing with no handholds  enid s purpose was to fashion together some kind of rope using the church crap so they could climb down the other side of the wall where presumably there were few or no zombies and they would have a better chance to escape  i ca nt remember if maggie got hurt or not before she got up there  but it sounds like from some comments she was  so again  it makes more sense for her to stay where there s at least a railing and room to hang out  if the platform was really about to collapse  maggie would have obviously gone onto the metal thing  or if there was no other option  jumped over the wall and probably broken some bones  which would probably have ended up killing her eventually as she d not be able to runfight off walkers so it made more sense for her to stay put until the horde had passed an injury can mean death in this world  as evidenced by that stupid girl a few episodes back who twisted her ankle and got eaten later that episode when they were trying to draw the horde to the quarry  the whole thing with the horde making the platform shake and glenn panicking was just drama for the sake of tv and yes  that was dumb  but it made for a more exciting scene than maggie calmly dragging herself on to the metal thing and laying down until the situation was sorted  as for getting up and killing zombies later if she was injured  maybe that s lazy writing  or maybe her injury was nt that bad  or it was just adrenaline kicking in  there s been dumber things on this show than this metal railingplatform thing so it did nt bother me much

text: i know i m late  we get it a day late here in the uk  i ve read a lot of comments about it being  one of  the best episodes  but honestly  i tink it is by far the greatest and here s why  1 as an avid comic reader  i m still constanty surprised by what happens this episode made me forget the comics were even a thing i could nt figure out the next move at any point  2 they knew full damn well that they could nt pull that  glenn survives  shit again  yet they still pulled it i was honestly an emotional wreck during the scene where he s backed up against the wall i could nt rationalise because of it and thats how they once again  fucked me over  3 gabriel had to redeem himself that quote  god has saved our town  because he s given us the courage to save it ourselves  is the most honest message twd has ever given to us  4 rick was wrong  and he admits it the faith everybody put into him and he gave them nothing back but shit he finally realised what the town is and this  not to spoil the comics  is the most important thing it had to happen  because if it did nt  you can just forget about  all out war  5 carls eye  needs nothing more  6 this is the last one i swear but the whole thing was so seemless 1 by 1 each group in hiding figured out what had to be done the whole episode made perfect sense from start to finish it was so emotional and if it was nt for 6 years of character development  it would nt have worked small details  michonne kissing carl  glenn looking for weapons  abe being abe  showed how much they all mean to each other and why they had to survive this

text: i thought the episode was good  fast paced  lots of action  etc and it answered a lot of questions  too many questions in my opinion they closed out what maybe 8 or 9 story lines i was watching and thought  snip  snip  snip   daryl and crew out of trouble  jessie and ron  and poor sam  and those romance subplots gone  the wolf gone  morgan  s  previously inexplicable  sympathy for the wolf is now justified and now carol looks even more ruthlesscrazy  gabriel is for some reason now trusted  wtf     eugene suddenly grew a pair  morgan is not longer a pacifist  denise somehow turned into a real doctor  maggie out of trouble  glenn shows off his plot armor  the gang is all back together  it seems to me that they spent the first half of this season creating a bunch of loose ends and questions  and wrapped up pretty much all of them in a single episode  in a way this is satisfying to me because i was getting tired of all of the open questions  but to wrap everything up so quickly and nicely seemed a bit forced to me

text: i know i am going to be bashed to oblivion for this but for me it was one of the worst episodes of the walking dead  coming from someone who has overall enjoyed the entire show so far  with some episodes being weaker than others of course   but i just have to get it off my chest  first thing that annoyed me  slightly   was that somehow no one heard daryl struggling with the guy  hell why did they even let daryl go 1 on 1 with the guy  that s obviously a terrible idea considering you expect there to be guns but this was a really minor issue and daryl blowing up that bunch was far worth it  now onto my real gripes with the episode  mid season finale cliff hanger with sam calling for  mom   scrapped what the hell  after that  ok rick s group walks out in the middle of the day  yet hours later in the pitch black night they are still walking through alexandria  again what  and here comes the nasty  i do not give one care about sam getting killed but seriously the whole scene played out so dumbly  it s just a goddamn kid  dude pick him up  shut his mouth or simply drag him by force or better yet knock his ass unconcious and carry him i have seen moms more fiercely force a kid on the sidewalk in a regular day than these people they just turned off their brains  i mean it s fine that the mom does it but one would think rickcarlmichonne would come with a better solution than trying to convince an unstable  panicking kid in the middle of a horde than by talking to him why not at least hug him and cover his eyes  drag him like that  what the fuck happened to any kind of logic  and then jessie freaks out  understandable  yet again rickcarlmichonne just stand there like idiots while jessie attracts the whole horde on them so rick just freaked out as well  after seeing all the shit from all seasons and being in his most hardened state  after telling so much how these people are hopeless and wo nt make it like 2 hours earlier now he freaks out because the kid whose death could be seen from a mile away got killed  great  and then prick teenager freaks out and decides to gun carl  i mean why does he even still have a gun  but whatever  carl had a brain fart on that and left the teenager who tried to kill him armed with a gun despite endagering everyone including judith by that teenagers i guess but then great michonne decides to take care of him  finally something nearly logical  too bad she had to dispose of him in the most nonlethal way to give him enough time to shoot carl  oh and to let him possibly die a horrible dead while he s eaten alive instead of going for a switf instant kill by like stabbing his head or something like that  she s the sword expert not me   but well heat of the moment i guess and at least carl s going to get a sweet eye patch  and then even more  glenn with his suicidal charge to save his wife oh wait here comes ginger with his automatic rifle and hits every zombie in the head going full auto  even the ones that were like 1 meter away from glenn  dude s obviously cheating with an aimbot   and yay glenn once again avoids certain doom in a ridiculous fashion  and then rick goes on a solo killing spree to  inspire  the alexandrians  cough  psychotic attack  cough   first how did he even last more than 5 seconds is beyond me  i guess the hundreds zombies were leaving a convenient path for rick to keep walking through without surrounding him  despite we have seen that s not how the horde acts in other episodes where they relentlessly and brutally surround people without leaving gaps  whatever these zombies just cassualy try to attack rick but mostly just keep passively wandering around like nothing s up then some more people go to  what i presumed  was rescuing rick from getting killed except not rick s senseless actions somehow inspired everyone into jumping to certain deaths  before the fire was even set   and what s worse is that it worked  they killed off thousands of zombies in melee range  not one weapon got stuck in a zombie s head  not one guy tripped in a zombie corspe  not a single guy got distracted or too tired to go on they melee bashed zombie skulls the entire night without a single casualty  even the inept alexandrians turned into spartan mode both courage and skill wise at least after the fire was set on it made more sense but the first bunch of people just happily went to their deaths  oh and good idea to use a rocket launcher just to light some fuel daryl cool i guess  that and now fire now apparently draws zombies to just literally walk to their deaths  why does nt rick just go with a smelly poncho a make a few fires here and there boom whole city is cleared from zombies i do nt even know how they will ever make zombie s look like a remotely threating force after this  this was the darkest and direst scenario and they solved it just like this after the midseason finale our characters can apparently hack through hundreds of zombies with just a few people  and they can just light a fire while wearing ponchos  without unstable teenagers  to solve any big horde problem anyway implying the show wo nt just make them forget i know from this ranting post it sounds like i hate the show or something but no i am usually willing to overlook plenty of things for the sake of story telling but this episode just went on and on and on with constant sillyness and mostly for senseless gratification even i expect some degree of realism and logic from this show  considering it has mostly been logical with few forgivable exceptions up to this episode it just felt like the show turned from a semirealistic zombie drama to michael bay s the walking dead  but with low budget explosions
